\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. P. doerfleri} Hayek,{\i  Denkschr. Akad. Wiss. Math.-Nat. Kl.} ({\i Wien}) {\b 94}: 196 (1917). Leaves orbicular-cordate, tomentose above; basal lobes divergent, without lateral vein-branches bordering the sinus; margin regularly toothed. Scapes with 4 or more scale-leaves, the lower almost sheathing at the base, the middle c. 1·5 cm, fewer than half with a rudimentary lamina. Capitula 3-10; involucre 8-10 mm; bracts purplish, pubescent, with an entire to somewhat fimbriate apex. Stigma of male florets 1·5-2 mm, not bifid to the base. Florets pale yellow or reddish. Ligules in the male 5-6 mm.{\i  Wet screes. • N. Albania} ({\i Bjëshket e Nemura}). Al ?Ju.
